The article is a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Congress, transmitting an Agreement to Extend the Agreement for Cooperation between the United States of America and the Republic of South Africa Concerning Peaceful Uses of Nuclear Energy. The Agreement, negotiated in accordance with the Atomic Energy Act of 1954, extends the previous agreement for four years. It allows for the transfer of material, equipment, and information for nuclear research and power production, with certain restrictions on sensitive technology and data. The Republic of South Africa, a member of the Nuclear Suppliers Group, has demonstrated its commitment to nuclear nonproliferation and disarmament. The President has reviewed the Agreement and determined that it promotes common defense and security. The letter requests favorable consideration from Congress and indicates that consultations will begin with the relevant committees.